<!--
    Vietnamese (vi) — translated from values-de/ (German source of truth).

    Script notes:
    • Vietnamese uses an extended Latin alphabet (Chữ Quốc ngữ) with a large
      set of combining diacritics: acute (´), grave (`), hook (̉), tilde (~),
      and dot-below (.) applied to six base vowels (a, ă, â, e, ê, i, o, ô,
      ơ, u, ư, y) plus the letter đ. All characters are Unicode and render
      correctly on Android without extra font configuration.
    • Register: polite (lịch sự) using "bạn" (you, informal-polite) as is
      standard for Vietnamese consumer app UIs.
    • "Binge drinking" → uống quá nhiều (public-health phrasing in Vietnamese).
    • DHS is kept as "DHS"; WHO as "WHO" (both used in Vietnamese public health).
    • day_change_time_value: Vietnamese uses no clock suffix in 24-hour format;
      HH:MM is used as-is.
    • Tonal marks are essential for meaning — every diacritic must be preserved
      exactly. Do NOT strip diacritics when editing this file.
-->
